\text{Volume} = \frac{1}{3}\text{base area} \times \text{height}. 
\]So, you need to find the areas of the bases. First, you must have the base length. We can use $$V = 63960$$\\ For 30 ft of height, the base length will be base area will be height cubed: \[
63960 = \frac{1}{3}\times\text{base area} \times \text{height}.
\]Let the base length be x. Then, $$\frac{1}{3}\times x^2\times \left(\frac{1}{3}x\right) = 63960$$\\ $$\frac{x^3}{9} =  63960$$\\ $$\Rightarrow  x^3 = 575640$$\\ $$\Rightarrow x = 83.7$$\\ Now that the base length is known, you need to use Pythagorean Theorem.  We know that $$a^2 + b^2 = c^2. $$\\ In this case, let the square root of the base length be a, and the height of the pyramid be b so that $$a^2 + b^2  =c^2\\ $$is the hypotenuse.$$ $$(\sqrt{83.7})^2 + (30)^2 = c^2\\ $$ Solving this equation, we get $$(83.7)^2 + (30)^2 = c^2\\ (6995.69) + 900 = c^2 (7895.69)+ (30)^2 = c^2\\ $$ $$(c^2) = 7895.69\\ \sqrt{7895.69} = c$$ Instant qusestion answer ---->  88.



